<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,284,830]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Discussion: It is tempting to consider this species as a local, well­marked form of the widely distributed and variable 
<taxonomicName box="[638,750,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paragrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugatulus">
<emphasis box="[638,750,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">rugatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the very consistent body form and different male genitalia make 
<taxonomicName box="[508,598,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paragrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguus">
<emphasis box="[508,598,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">exiguus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinct.
</paragraph>
